***LIST***.
Merced County grows 90% of California's sweet potato crop, due in part to the efforts of John Buttencourt Avila, called "the father of the sweet potato industry".
========,2,Transportation.
========,3,Airports.
Merced Regional Airport, located two miles (3 km) southwest of downtown Merced, provides passenger air service.
General aviation airports in the county include Castle Airport, Gustine Airport, and Los Banos Municipal Airport.
